# .env.example — documents environment variables this project expects.
# Copy to ".env" (which is gitignored) and fill in real values locally.
#
# As of Phase 0 the site is fully static and needs NO secrets or env vars.
# This file exists from the first commit so the secrets-handling habit is in
# place before anything sensitive is ever introduced.
#
# The moment a build key, form backend, or third-party API is added, document
# it HERE first (name + one-line purpose), and flag it in the commit message —
# never paste a real value into a tracked file.

# (no variables required yet)
